parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or dies while driving
the engine is difficult to start or will not start
the vehicle experiences a loss of power
the fuel pump makes a loud whining or grinding noise
the fuel pump is leaking fuel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Broken exhaust manifold studs can cause the cylinder head to crack, resulting in exhaust flames spewing towards the passenger floorboard, which can lead to a fire hazard and potentially injure occupants.
symptoms: Exhaust flames visible from the passenger floorboard
cracked cylinder head
broken exhaust manifold studs.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling in High Temperatures and Altitudes
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause a loss of power and control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially in high-temperature and high-altitude conditions.
symptoms: Engine stops running while driving
loss of power
difficulty restarting the engine
stalling in high-temperature and high-altitude conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure - Exposed Cable Shorting
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An exposed cable shorting on the propane line can cause an electrical fire, leading to a risk of vehicle damage, injury, or even fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle has no generator
exposed cables are visible
electrical system malfunctions
unusual burning smells or smoke
sparks or flames near the propane line.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An improperly installed roof pod or accessory can detach from the vehicle while in motion, causing damage to the vehicle and surrounding property, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The roof pod or accessory becomes loose or detached while driving
causing noise
vibration
or loss of control; the roof pod or accessory falls off the vehicle
causing damage or obstruction on the road.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the dealer to take responsibility for improper installations or repairs can lead to frustration, financial loss, and potential safety risks for the vehicle owner.
symptoms: Dealer refuses to acknowledge or repair issues related to improper installation; dealer denies warranty coverage for repairs; vehicle owner experiences difficulty in getting issues resolved with the dealer.
